#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:176
msgid "Create a new spider in the current project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:178
msgid ""
"This is just a convenient shortcut command for creating spiders based on pre-"
"defined templates, but certainly not the only way to create spiders. You can "
"just create the spider source code files yourself, instead of using this "
"command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:185
msgid ""
"$ scrapy genspider -l\n"
"Available templates:\n"
"  basic\n"
"  crawl\n"
"  csvfeed\n"
"  xmlfeed\n"
"\n"
"$ scrapy genspider -d basic\n"
"import scrapy\n"
"\n"
"class $classname(scrapy.Spider):\n"
"    name = \"$name\"\n"
"    allowed_domains = [\"$domain\"]\n"
"    start_urls = (\n"
"        'http://www.$domain/',\n"
"        )\n"
"\n"
"    def parse(self, response):\n"
"        pass\n"
"\n"
"$ scrapy genspider -t basic example example.com\n"
"Created spider 'example' using template 'basic' in module:\n"
"  mybot.spiders.example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:212
msgid "crawl"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:214
msgid "Syntax: ``scrapy crawl <spider>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:217
msgid "Start crawling using a spider."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:219 ../../../topics/commands.rst:235
#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:308
msgid "Usage examples::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:221
msgid ""
"$ scrapy crawl myspider\n"
"[ ... myspider starts crawling ... ]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:228
msgid "check"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:230
msgid "Syntax: ``scrapy check [-l] <spider>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:233
msgid "Run contract checks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:237
msgid ""
"$ scrapy check -l\n"
"first_spider\n"
"  * parse\n"
"  * parse_item\n"
"second_spider\n"
"  * parse\n"
"  * parse_item\n"
"\n"
"$ scrapy check\n"
"[FAILED] first_spider:parse_item\n"
">>> 'RetailPricex' field is missing\n"
"\n"
"[FAILED] first_spider:parse\n"
">>> Returned 92 requests, expected 0..4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:255
msgid "list"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:257
msgid "Syntax: ``scrapy list``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:260
msgid ""
"List all available spiders in the current project. The output is one spider "
"per line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:265
msgid ""
"$ scrapy list\n"
"spider1\n"
"spider2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:272
msgid "edit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:274
msgid "Syntax: ``scrapy edit <spider>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:277
msgid ""
"Edit the given spider using the editor defined in the :setting:`EDITOR` "
"setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:280
msgid ""
"This command is provided only as a convenient shortcut for the most common "
"case, the developer is of course free to choose any tool or IDE to write and "
"debug his spiders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:286
msgid "$ scrapy edit spider1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:291
msgid "fetch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:293
msgid "Syntax: ``scrapy fetch <url>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:296
msgid ""
"Downloads the given URL using the Scrapy downloader and writes the contents "
"to standard output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:299
msgid ""
"The interesting thing about this command is that it fetches the page how the "
"spider would download it. For example, if the spider has an ``USER_AGENT`` "
"attribute which overrides the User Agent, it will use that one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:303
msgid ""
"So this command can be used to \"see\" how your spider would fetch a certain "
"page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:305
msgid ""
"If used outside a project, no particular per-spider behaviour would be "
"applied and it will just use the default Scrapy downloader settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:310
msgid ""
"$ scrapy fetch --nolog http://www.example.com/some/page.html\n"
"[ ... html content here ... ]\n"
"\n"
"$ scrapy fetch --nolog --headers http://www.example.com/\n"
"{'Accept-Ranges': ['bytes'],\n"
" 'Age': ['1263   '],\n"
" 'Connection': ['close     '],\n"
" 'Content-Length': ['596'],\n"
" 'Content-Type': ['text/html; charset=UTF-8'],\n"
" 'Date': ['Wed, 18 Aug 2010 23:59:46 GMT'],\n"
" 'Etag': ['\"573c1-254-48c9c87349680\"'],\n"
" 'Last-Modified': ['Fri, 30 Jul 2010 15:30:18 GMT'],\n"
" 'Server': ['Apache/2.2.3 (CentOS)']}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:327
msgid "view"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:329
msgid "Syntax: ``scrapy view <url>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:332
msgid ""
"Opens the given URL in a browser, as your Scrapy spider would \"see\" it. "
"Sometimes spiders see pages differently from regular users, so this can be "
"used to check what the spider \"sees\" and confirm it's what you expect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:338
msgid ""
"$ scrapy view http://www.example.com/some/page.html\n"
"[ ... browser starts ... ]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:344
msgid "shell"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:346
msgid "Syntax: ``scrapy shell [url]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:349
msgid ""
"Starts the Scrapy shell for the given URL (if given) or empty if no URL is "
"given. See :ref:`topics-shell` for more info."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:354
msgid ""
"$ scrapy shell http://www.example.com/some/page.html\n"
"[ ... scrapy shell starts ... ]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:360
msgid "parse"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:362
msgid "Syntax: ``scrapy parse <url> [options]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:365
msgid ""
"Fetches the given URL and parses it with the spider that handles it, using "
"the method passed with the ``--callback`` option, or ``parse`` if not given."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:368
msgid "Supported options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:370
msgid ""
"``--spider=SPIDER``: bypass spider autodetection and force use of specific "
"spider"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:372
msgid "``--a NAME=VALUE``: set spider argument (may be repeated)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:374
msgid ""
"``--callback`` or ``-c``: spider method to use as callback for parsing the "
"response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:377
msgid "``--pipelines``: process items through pipelines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:379
msgid ""
"``--rules`` or ``-r``: use :class:`~scrapy.contrib.spiders.CrawlSpider` "
"rules to discover the callback (i.e. spider method) to use for parsing the "
"response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:383
msgid "``--noitems``: don't show scraped items"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:385
msgid "``--nolinks``: don't show extracted links"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:387
msgid "``--nocolour``: avoid using pygments to colorize the output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:389
msgid ""
"``--depth`` or ``-d``: depth level for which the requests should be followed "
"recursively (default: 1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:392
msgid "``--verbose`` or ``-v``: display information for each depth level"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:396
msgid ""
"$ scrapy parse http://www.example.com/ -c parse_item\n"
"[ ... scrapy log lines crawling example.com spider ... ]\n"
"\n"
">>> STATUS DEPTH LEVEL 1 <<<\n"
"# Scraped Items  "
"------------------------------------------------------------\n"
"[{'name': u'Example item',\n"
" 'category': u'Furniture',\n"
" 'length': u'12 cm'}]\n"
"\n"
"# Requests  "
"-----------------------------------------------------------------\n"
"[]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:412
msgid "settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:414
msgid "Syntax: ``scrapy settings [options]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:417
msgid "Get the value of a Scrapy setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:419
msgid ""
"If used inside a project it'll show the project setting value, otherwise "
"it'll show the default Scrapy value for that setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:422 ../../../topics/commands.rst:440
msgid "Example usage::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:424
msgid ""
"$ scrapy settings --get BOT_NAME\n"
"scrapybot\n"
"$ scrapy settings --get DOWNLOAD_DELAY\n"
"0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:432
msgid "runspider"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/commands.rst:434
msgid "Syntax: ``scrapy runspider <spider_file.py>``"
